				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How much song range extension is too much?<a name="74369"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 13 05 7:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Songs don't break FD. The issue is if they get hit with a song buff before they FD. You now have aggro and this could train the raid. 
<br />

<br />
If the pullers are good about calling their pulls, you should be able to avoid this. In our raids we have a pull channel that has anyone who needs to know what's going on there in it. That includes the raid leader, the MT, the head cleric and CC. And me, since bards are our main pullers in most situations. It's as much their responsiblity to call songs off as it is yours to stop playing. They know when they're going to be close enough for the raid for it to matter.
<br />

<br />
My understanding is that Extended Notes 3, increases the range of all your benefical songs by 25%. Scionachie's Cresendo gives a greater extention but only to group only songs, so unless the monk puller is in your group, it won't matter. The extra range there helps you buff the MT, but stay out of a small range AE. Or still be buffing him while melee'ing behind the mob.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
