				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How much song range extension is too much?<a name="75216"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 05 5:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have both the max range AAs.  In a group situation, it rarely is a problem if your group is awake.  In a raid situation, if you are not on the pull team, then don't group with your pullers.  There is alot more aggro if you are twisting.  Otherwise, just be alert.  When you know multis are inc, turn off AE until mobs in camp.  Max range is great if you are in a MT group and need to stay just out of boss's AE range.  Encounters like Xegony and RZtW are much easier when bards have max range on group songs.</span></td>
